Package gym

Class FitnessClass

java.lang.Object
fitness_classes.FitnessClass
public class FitnessClass extends Object
This class defines a fitness class and has access to all other fitness classes that exist. The fitness classes are pre-defined and constant, but the properties of those fitness classes like the people in those fitness classes is variable. This class facilitates that entire process.
Author:
Hasnain Ali, Carolette Saguil

  • Field Details

    • classSize

      private static int[] classSize
      Corresponding to membersInClass; stores how many people are in each class corresponding to the main membersInClass database.

    • membersInClass

      private static Member[][] membersInClass
      Stores all the members in all the fitness classes.
      • membersInClass[0] stores Pilates class members
      • membersInClass[1] stores Spinning class members
      • membersInClass[2] stores Cardio class members
      Each index stores in membersInClass[index] stores the members in that class.

    • FITNESS_CLASS

      private final Time FITNESS_CLASS
      Stores the current FitnessClass's instance Time enum for the specific class. Effectively, this lets the current FitnessClass instance store the name of the current fitness class.

    • ALL_CLASSES

      private final Time[] ALL_CLASSES
      Stores all the Time enums for all the FitnessClasses. This is effectively, so we can get the name of any time conflicting classes.

  • Constructor Details

    • FitnessClass

      public FitnessClass(Time time)
      Initializes a 2D static array for the members in the class. Creates a membersInClass 2D array for membersInClass[x] where x is the class index for the fitness class and membersInClass[x][y] where y is the index of the member in that particular fitness class. Thus, for example, membersInClass[0][0] represents the first member in the Pilates class since membersInClass[0] represents all the students in Pilates.
        membersInClass[0] = Pilates, membersInClass[1] = Spinning, membersInClass[2] = Cardio
      This constructor stores time in the class too for future use. Additionally, this class stores how big each class in the membersInClass database is so far, in case it need to dynamically grow the class later. Additionally, this class stores all the times defined in Time enum to be used for later. The indexes for each class are the same as above where 0 is Pilates, 1 is Spinning, and 2 is Cardio. These values do not change throughout the program.
      Parameters:
      time - Time enum for specifically designed for the fitness class.

    • checkIn

      Parameters:

      Returns:

    • printClassSchedule
